# Summary

<div class="block">

![Visualization](/img/diagrams/calculus/midpoint-rule.png)
    
An approximation of an integral can be performed as such:
$$ \int_a^bf(x)dx \approx M_n = \Delta{x}\left[f(\bar{x}_1) + f(\bar{x}_2) + \cdots + f(\bar{x}_n)\right] $$
where
$$ \Delta{x}=\frac{b-a}{n}\text{ and }\bar{x}_i=\frac{1}{2}(x_{i-1}+x_i)=\text{ midpoint of }[x_{i-1}, x_i]. $$

</div>

